00553 
00554 double CatenaryProblem::calculatePotentialEnergyIntegrand(double x, double dummy)
00555 {
00556    double potentialEnergyIntegrand = 0.0;
00557 
00558    Vector<double> input(1);
00559    Vector<double> output(1);
00560    Matrix<double> jacobian(1, 1);
00561 
00562    input[0] = x;
00563    output = multilayerPerceptron->calculateOutput(input, *this);
00564 
00565     double y = output[0];
00566 
00567    jacobian = multilayerPerceptron->calculateJacobian(input, *this);
00568 
00569     double dydx = jacobian[0][0];
00570 
00571    potentialEnergyIntegrand = y*sqrt(1.0 + pow(dydx,2));
00572 
00573    return(potentialEnergyIntegrand);

00584 
00585 double CatenaryProblem::calculatePotentialEnergy(void)
00586 {
00587    double potentialEnergy = 0.0;
00588 
00589    Vector<double> x;
00590    Vector<double> y;
00591 
00592    int numberOfPoints = 
00593    ordinaryDifferentialEquations.calculateRungeKuttaFehlbergIntegral(*this,
00594    x, y, 
00595    &CatenaryProblem::calculatePotentialEnergyIntegrand,
00596    xA, xB, 0.0);
00597 
00598    potentialEnergy = y[numberOfPoints-1];
00599 
00600    return(potentialEnergy);

00686                 << std::endl;

00688         exit(1);

00694

00696 
00697    numberOfEvaluations++;
00698 
00699    double potentialEnergy = calculatePotentialEnergy();
